Sentencas: NiO-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (NiO-10GDC) nanocomposite anode material was synthesized through combustion technique for possible low temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Combustion synthesis of NiO-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 nanocomposite anode and its electrical characteristics of semi-cell configured SOFC assembly

Sentencas: A low weight loss is seen in the TG/DTA thermogram that indicates the complete combustion of the reactant mixtures.

Sentencas: The powder X-ray diffraction patterns showed that the presence of NiO, GDC and Ni crystallite phases in the as combusted product.
Titulo: Combustion synthesis of NiO-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 nanocomposite anode and its electrical characteristics of semi-cell configured SOFC assembly

Sentencas: Upon calcination at 600 degrees C, the metallic Ni oxidized to NiO. TEM images showed a wide size distribution of fine spherical GDC and large irregularly shaped NiO particles.
Titulo: Combustion synthesis of NiO-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 nanocomposite anode and its electrical characteristics of semi-cell configured SOFC assembly
